{
  "machine_name": "Lean4 compiler pipeline (parser, elaborator, kernel, LCNF code generator)",
  "assembly_instructions": "Build left-to-right (+X) along a single steel frame rail that carries the whole compilation pipeline; a copper flow spine runs above it as the dataflow bus. Bolt the front-end blocks to the rail in order: source_file (glass, input text) → parser (steel, Pratt/syntax-category parser) → syntax_tree (glass, hygienic Syntax objects), with the macro_expander standing off to +Z and a flat black torus (macro_loop) closing the parse↔expand fixpoint back onto the parser. Next mount the elaborator, a large steel block flanked by its services: metavar_ctx (white, buffer) at +Z, unifier (steel, defeq/higher-order unification) at −Z, tc_synth (brass, tabled type-class instance table) at +Z, tactic_framework (black, control) at −Z; a vertical black torus (elab_loop) above spans elaborator→expr_core to show the postponement/synthesis fixpoint. The elaborated expr_core (glass, Expr in CIC) feeds the kernel (steel, ~6k-line trusted checker) which admits declarations into the environment (brass, learned/stored declarations), serialized sideways into olean_store (white, mmap'd .olean) and executable through the interpreter (black) at −Z. From the environment the back end continues along the rail as a chain of distinct LCNF passes — lcnf_lower, lcnf_simp, lcnf_spec, lcnf_erase, rc_insert — each its own block rather than one 'optimizer' box, ending in ir_emit (glass) and c_codegen (steel), with runtime_rc (white) attached below-right as the reference-counting runtime the emitted C links against.",
