  critique: The render exposed three real defects. (1) The frame was ONE chassis box (`frame_rail`), and the copper `flow_spine` hung 1.2 m above every block on nothing — the SIDE view shows it as a bare floating stick; the ±2.5 m service blocks (metavar_ctx, unifier, tc_synth, olean_store, interpreter, runtime_rc) sat on bare ground with no member joining them to the rail, so TOP reads as three disconnected rows of scattered cubes. (2) The FRONT elevation was a monotone row of ~14 identical grey rectangles: the five LCNF passes were the same size and the same `welded steel`, so the back end carried no information at all. (3) Against the authoritative Fig. 3.1 the scene was simply incomplete — the **pretty printer**, **language server**, **editor** and the **module system** are named components of the pipeline and were all absent, as was the bootstrap feedback (code generator emitting metaprograms that run inside the frontend for subsequent input) and the frontend/kernel/code-generator zoning the thesis states explicitly. Also `flow_spine` at y=2.6 passed straight through the elaborator's volume.
  + Closed the carried-over source-fidelity gap: added `pretty_printer`, `language_server` and `editor` from thesis Fig. 3.1 on a raised gantry over the front end, and `module_system` (§3.3, imports loaded from already-compiled .olean files) feeding the parser.
  + Added `bootstrap_loop` — the interpreter/code-generator feedback that makes emitted metaprograms part of the component processing subsequent input, the defining Lean-in-Lean property.
  + Replaced the single chassis box with a real frame: two rails (`frame_rail`, `rail_back`), a thin `deck_plate` floor, three `pedestal_*` posts, two `service_deck_*` plinths and two `tie_*` floor beams so no service block floats unconnected.
  + Zoned the floor into three concrete/brass pads (`frontend_pad`, `tcb_pad`, `backend_pad`) after the thesis's explicit boundary: everything except the kernel and code generator is the frontend.
  + Raised `flow_spine` to y=3.4 and put it on three real posts — it no longer intersects the elaborator and no longer floats.
  + Differentiated the LCNF chain: heights now descend 1.5→1.35→1.25→1.10 as types and proofs are erased, `rc_insert`/`runtime_rc` recoloured copper to bind the reference-counting subsystem together.
  + Compressed the X span to ±7.9 and made both fixpoint tori flat/horizontal so they encircle the stages they close over instead of cutting through them.
  · gap: The kernel is still one opaque `forged steel` block: split its interior legibly (whnf/defeq engine, inductive-type compiler, universe checker) as an exploded stack directly above it with `role` saying so — this is the last real X-ray failure.
  · gap: The elaborator is also a solid 1.5×2.2×1.5 block; consider rebuilding it as an open bay (four posts + top plate) with metavar_ctx pulled inside it, since the metavariable context is genuinely interior working memory, not a side service.
  · gap: `macro_loop`, `elab_loop` and `bootstrap_loop` hover with no riser touching the blocks they span; add a short standoff from each loop down to one stage so the elevation views read them as attached control paths.
  · gap: Verify in the next render that `spine_post_mid` at x=0.6 really clears environment (ends 0.5) and lcnf_lower (starts 0.675) — the gap is only 0.175 m and may look like interpenetration.
  · gap: Dimensions are schematic block sizes, not traceable to a spec; consider encoding real magnitudes (kernel ~6k LoC, LCNF pass count) into `spec.params` on the relevant parts to lift the buildability axis.

